Name: Plasmodium ovale malaria
Definition: A malaria characaterized as a relatively mild form caused by a parasite Plasmodium ovale

Name: obsolete childhood schizophrenia
Definition: A malaria characaterized as a relatively mild form caused by a parasite Plasmodium ovale

Name: obsolete acute undifferentiated schizophrenia
Definition: A malaria characaterized as a relatively mild form caused by a parasite Plasmodium ovale

Name: obsolete chronic undifferentiated schizophrenia
Definition: A malaria characaterized as a relatively mild form caused by a parasite Plasmodium ovale

Name: Plasmodium vivax malaria
Definition: A malaria that is caused by the protozoan parasite Plasmodium vivax

Name: obsolete transient disorder of initiating or maintaining sleep
Definition: A malaria that is caused by the protozoan parasite Plasmodium vivax

Name: Plasmodium falciparum malaria
Definition: A malaria described as a severe form of the disease caused by a parasite Plasmodium falciparum

Name: blackwater fever
Definition: A malaria that presents as a rare febrile complication of repeated malarial attacks characterized by intravascular haemolysis

Name: cerebral malaria
Definition: A malaria that involves neurologic damage resulting from blockage of the blood vessels

Name: Plasmodium malariae malaria
Definition: A malaria caused by a parasite Plasmodium malariae

Name: mixed malaria
Definition: A malaria that involves infection with more than one species of Plasmodium at the same time.
Synonym: Malaria fever by more than one parasite

Name: obsolete avian malaria
Definition: A malaria characterized as a vector-borne infectious disease of birds caused by protozoan parasites Plasmodium relictum

Name: obsolete gonococcal pericarditis
Definition: A malaria characterized as a vector-borne infectious disease of birds caused by protozoan parasites Plasmodium relictum
